Here&#x27;s a stupid one.  I keep getting lost what I was doing in each of 20 screen windows.  So I keep a &quot;goal&quot; per shell that appears in the $PS1 for each.<p><pre><code>  goal () 
  { 
    if [ $# -gt 0 ]; then
        MYGOAL=&quot;$@&quot;;
    else
        echo Your current goal is: $MYGOAL;
    fi
  }
</code></pre>
That&#x27;s it.  Put ($MYGOAL) in your PS1 and type &quot;goal fix this bug&quot; or &quot;goal working on that thing&quot;.  No args just echos back (redundant).
